spanGrp.span: ‘I saw that the place looks nice.
There were trees and there was a man; it looks nice.
Kal juer-gẽ jeyiwa kalu juer-gẽ bá
Some children were playing with a snake.
The snake seems to be very nice.
Je í rö jũ kate böi
in a far place, under the trees and things it spreads out nicely all the way till it becomes blue.
kã' komĩ' jera kã' komĩ' jera kal digĩ jirö digĩ (_) sige-nã bá ramã sige-nã köũ siu ramã
But it is not the way we see it.
Jebi se je të í sũẽ-ra í rö ka rö jebi
Inside the computer the children were playing with a snake;
tebeli_yaga jãrga ra bá peyabla jinõ kebé ra
it is a big snake, it itself is big.
kebé wagi rö keyege kebé wagi rö keyege
That child/it flies with the child.
Je nẽ yaba/ (_) jũr-gẽ yaba ra ro
The house was nice and I see it would be nice if we had a place like that.
Jemẽ nẽ ra pe jũ kate bá yís sũã' rö jebi se je ĩã kã' telë-wã-pa rö
But our place is not like that.
Tara ka se je/ ka se je ka rö jebi kunã
But that one is very nice.
Pero je rö bá ramã köũ
I saw it all like that.’
jebi yís të kable sũã' rö
